cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes an unsupervised paradigm for deep visual odometry learning, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks and loss functions, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with the estimation of camera pose, which is a problem in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely category. Finally, the paper presents a method for characterizing uncertainty, which is a topic in statistics and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category.
